{
  "stem": "8892.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And slaughters the cows or cattles and all that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father would take over after and, you know, cut it up and portion it, or they skin it and then sell the leather-- the skin to the leather guys, and the inside guts to another company.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my father would go and from every-- well, at least once a month, he risked our family, he risked his life, and would bring [NON-ENGLISH] from a different town.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then when he gets off the train, the town people cannot recognize him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He's just another ordinary Jew coming to the little town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he would pick him up, bring him to the house, go to the barn and do just small things like a lamb or maybe two calves.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then he would go, nighttime, in the butcher shop and sort it out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I don't know if you know that a half a meat is-- half side of the cattle is kosher and a half isn't.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So the half would go out to the Gentiles during the Sunday or whatever.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Three times a week he had to serve them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the rest he just portioned it out and sent them out by us, us kids-- my little brother, me-- because we were the ones that were home.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And little packages, and one went for the rabbi family, one went for the-- first was the family taken care of, the uncles and aunts.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And actually he spread it out that everybody got one or 2 kilos, which is like 2, 3 pounds of meat for every Jew in town.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My mother, from that point on, was just beyond herself, nervous and shaking.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
